021.";i:5;s:128:"The Chair Netflixs new six-part dramedy set in the English department of a fictional Ivy League school is about a lot of things.";i:6;s:41:"Existing as a woman of color in academia.";i:7;s:25:"The CHAIR w Sandra Oh ps.";i:8;s:55:"Im on episode 2 of The Chair and Im enjoying it so far.";i:9;s:50:"Bill Dobson comes off as a douchey immature loser.";i:10;s:72:"Doesnt come off as intelligent even though hes a professor or something.";i:11;s:40:"And hes not funny or likable whatsoever.";i:12;s:221:"For those disappointed by the humorless and deeply earnest treatment of the contemporary campus experience in the 2020 TV adaptation of Sally Rooneys Normal People the new Netflix series The Chair will be a welcome tonic.";i:13;s:157:"Over its punchy six half-hour episodes the show co-created by the actress Amanda Peet and produced by her husband David Benioff deals with the iniquities of.";i:14;s:66:"Can someone enlighten me how Bill is a charming character because.";i:15;s:54:"Hes good to Ju Ju and a bit of a father figure to her.";i:16;s:42:"But apart from that hes an absolute prick.";i:17;s:191:"The drama revolves around Ji-Yoon Kim played by Sandra Oh who has just been appointed chair of a stuffy academic English department and is struggling to be heard by nearly all her colleagues.";i:18;s:181:"It feels like a genuine exploration a dramatised discussion of intergenerational differences and divides that few are seeking to take the heat out of and examine with real interest.";i:19;s:150:"These reviews clearly establish that The Chair s strength lies with Ji-Yoons compelling yet messy characterization and her even messier relationships.";i:20;s:187:"The Chair seems to suggest that the culture conflict between an increasingly social-justice focused student body and the historic dominance of white masculinity in academia is reaching a.";i:21;s:223:"The Chair star Sandra Oh and her cast mates Holland Taylor Jay Duplass Nana Mensah and Bob Balaban are joined by series creator Amanda Peet to discuss how they prepped for life on a college campus in their new Netflix show.";i:22;s:184:"Women of color in academia have had conflicting reactions to the Netflix series The Chair Some felt the storyline of Yazs tenure case undermined the challenges academics of color face.";i:23;s:94:"The show inspired debate about whether its important for fictional depictions to be realistic.";i:24;s:28:"Written By Original Content.";i:25;s:70:"This week we review The Chair a new Netflix series starring Sandra Oh.";i:26;s:61:"If youd like to skip ahead heres how the episode breaks down.";i:27;s:21:"129 The Chair review.";i:28;s:34:"2743 The Chair spoiler discussion.";i:29;s:324:"Nana Mensah Bob Balaban David Morse Among 10 Cast In Netflix Dramedy Series From Amanda Peet Game Of Thrones Creators By Denise Petski Netflix has rounded out cast for The Chair a new six-episode half-hour dramedy starring and executive produced by Killing Eve s Sandra Oh and co-starring Jay Duplass Transparent Outside In.";i:30;s:148:"The Chair - I think its a good show so far watched four episodes last night but I was put off because their offices and classrooms are way too nice.";i:31;s:42:"The furniture the art the books all of it.";i:32;s:41:"Even Ivy League campuses arent like that.";i:33;s:95:"Even senior faculty at rich schools teach in pretty bland looking corporate offices these days.";i:34;s:166:"Netflixs campus comedy The Chair starring Sandra Oh is elevated by a novel parenting crisis culturally specific workplace issues and irrepressible romantic chemistry.";i:35;s:30:"2021 TV-MA 1 Season TV Dramas.";i:36;s:152:"At a major university the first woman of color to become chair tries to meet the dizzying demands and high expectations of a failing English department.";i:37;s:37:"Sandra Oh Jay Duplass Holland Taylor.";i:38;s:97:"New Netflix drama The Chair is honest and funny but it still romanticizes modern university life.";i:39;s:167:"Still from The Chair Netf